[1] Romania
Date: 9 Jun 2006
From: ProMED-mail<promed@promedmail.org>
Source: OIE Disease Information, Vol. 19 - No. 23 [edited]
<http://www.oie.int/eng/info/hebdo/AIS_15.HTM>

Avian influenza in Romania: Follow-up report No. 2
Information received on 1 Jun 2006 from Dr
Gabriel Predoi, Director General, National
Sanitary Veterinary and Food Safety Authority, Bucharest:
End of this report period: 1 Jun 2006
Identification of agent: avian influenza virus subtype H5.
Date of start of the event: 6 May 2006.
New outbreaks: There were 57 outbreaks in 12
provinces including 23 in Prahova
province. Other provinces included Alba Arges
(2), Bacau (6), Brasov (11), Bucuresti (2),
Buzau, Gorj (2), Ilfov, Mures, Valcea (3),
Vrancea (3).The outbreaks involved 18 174 birds
resulting in 3723 deaths. All outbreaks were
between 13 May 2006 and 25 May 2006. [4
outbreaks were listed in May of 2005 but we can
only assume this was a typographical error. For
a map of the Romanian counties see
<http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Image:Romania_counties.png> - Mod. PC]
Description of affected population: backyard poultry.
Laboratory where diagnostic tests were performed:
Institute for Diagnosis and Animal Health
(national reference laboratory). Virus isolation was positive for subtype H5.
Source of outbreaks or origin of infection:
- illegal movement of animals;
- fomites (humans, vehicles, feed, etc.);
- contact with wild animals.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
