[4] Niger
Date: 9 Jun 2006
From: ProMED-mail<promed@promedmail.org>
Source: OIE Disease Information, Vol. 19 - No. 23 [edited]
<http://www.oie.int/eng/info/hebdo/AIS_15.HTM>

Avian influenza in Niger: Follow-up report No. 1
Translation of information received on 7 Jun 2006
from Dr Seini Aboubacar, Director for Animal
Health, Ministry of Animal Resources, Niamey:
End of this report period: 2 Jun 2006.
Identification of agent: highly pathogenic avian influenza virus subtype H5N1.
Date of start of the event: 13 Feb 2006.
New outbreak: A new outbreak involving 700 sick
birds of which 530 died was reported. 8000 birds
were susceptible. The outbreak occurred in Gabi
commune, Maradi region of Niger. <http://www.oie.int/cartes/19_23_NER_A.doc>
Description of affected population: backyard poultry (chickens).
Laboratory where diagnostic tests were performed:
OIE Reference Laboratory for avian influenza and
Newcastle disease in Padova, Italy
Results: RT-PCR (genes M, H5 and N1) and
sequence analysis was positive for H5N1. The
amino acid sequence at cleavage site reveals a HPAI profile
Source of outbreak or origin of infection: introduction of new live animals.
Other details/comments: Stamping out was
undertaken from 9 to 11 Apr 2006 in Magaria
district (previous reported outbreak).
Gabi commune is situated around 15 km from the northern border with Nigeria.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
******
[5] China
Date: 9 Jun 2006
From: ProMED-mail<promed@promedmail.org>
Source: OIE Disease Information, Vol. 19 - No. 23 [edited]
<http://www.oie.int/eng/info/hebdo/AIS_15.HTM>

Highly Pathogenic Avian Influenza In China
(People's Rep. Of ~) : Follow-up report No. 15
Information received on 7 Jun 2006 from Mr Jia
Youling, Director General, Veterinary Bureau, Ministry of Agriculture, Beijing:
End of this report period: 7 Jun 2006.
Identification of agent: highly pathogenic avian
influenza (HPAI) virus subtype H5N1.
Date of first confirmation of the event: 7 Jun 2005.
New outbreak: Xinjiang province, Hetian city has
been identified. 200 cases, all dying, out of 637 was reported.
Description of affected population: poultry.
Laboratory where diagnostic tests were performed:
Harbin Veterinary Research Institute, Chinese
Academy of Agricultural Sciences, Harbin
(national reference laboratory for avian influenza).
Results: haemagglutination inhibition test;
RT-PCR; and virus isolation were all positive on 7 Jun 2006.
--
